message: Added origin (if he is an Australian citizen, though not born, then he should at least have an Australian origin place), added Scottish-born, to clarify that being cited only as Australian gives the impression that he is Australian-born.
Fixed birthplace and added Scottish-born just to make clear he wasn't Australian-born.
/* 1955–1966: Music origins, Bee Gees formation and popularity in Australia */
/* Wee Johnny Hayes and the Blue Cats */ new section
Please don't confuse Welsh-born Australian with Welsh-Australian.
Don't confuse Scottish-born Australian with Scottish-Australian. Scottish-born Australians hold only one nationality (Australian).
Though the Young brothers were Scottish-born, their origin was Australia.

Scottish-born Australian isn't the same as Scottish-Australian. If you're Scottish-born Australian, then you're an Australian citizen, without holding dual citizenship, but it doesn't undo the fact that you were born in Scotland. If you're Scottish-Australian, then you hold dual nationality.
Sources say he's British, not English.
/* Bee Gees */ Fixed typo, Added links
/* 1955–1966: Music origins, Bee Gees formation and popularity in Australia */
/* 1955–1966: Music origins, Bee Gees formation and popularity in Australia */
They were not an English band (though consisting on English brothers), as the band is Australian-based.

page: The Bee Gees Sing and Play 14 Barry Gibb Songs
message: There is no problem in adding nationality, as there is no consensus on this page saying I can't nationality.
The Bee Gees must cited in this page, as they were part of the Australian music scene as well as part of the British music scene.
The decision of putting Scottish-born Australian is to make clear that, though he was an OZ citizen, he wasn't OZ-born.
Describing him only as Australian gives the impression that he was Australian-born, considering he is Scottish-born.
If he is English-born Australian, then he's exclusively an Australian citizen, so please stop edit warring. There is not such thing as English-Australian double citizenship.
Young was born in Cranhill. And as he is an Australian citizen, he should an Australian place of origin.
If he is an Australian citizen, then he must have an Australian origin place, which is Sydney.
Roger Daltrey is a Cockney by his accent.
Don't describe him as Scottish. He was born in Scotland but brought in England, making him British.
/* Young brothers (Angus, Malcolm, George), Bon Scott and Dave Evans */ new section
